Find partition to mount
    > lsblk
    or
    > sudo fdisk -l
    - will be /dev/sdXX - eg. /dev/sdc1

Find UUID for that partition
    > blkid

Create a mount point
    > sudo mkdir /media/david/MountDir
    - change ownership of mount point
    > sudo chown -R david:david /media/david/MountDir

Add automount entry
    > sudo nano /etc/fstab

Test if it works
    > sudo mount -a

For shared NTFS partitions
Create media user for sharing
    > sudo adduser media
Add david to media group
    > usermod -aG media david
